## Before your plumber arrives

A few steps make the visit faster and safer:

- Turn off the main water supply if you have an active leak and know where the valve is.
- Clear access under sinks, behind the commode, and around the geyser or tank.
- Note when the problem started and whether it is getting worse.
- List related issues in one booking when they can be handled in the same visit.
- Be home, or have someone available to show the problem and approve the work.

